// SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0 WITH LLVM-exception
//
// test/parse/grammar/function-keyword/pass-function.test
//
// US1 / FR-016 / `S26` parser-equivalence fixture pair (T032a) — the
// `function` spelling. The companion `pass-func.test` fixture
// exercises the `func` spelling on otherwise-identical input; the
// two AST snapshots MUST share the same `NodeKind` names and the
// same nesting shape. The byte-offsets in the printer's `loc=`
// field differ between the two fixtures by exactly the
// `len("function") - len("func") = 4` keyword-length delta — we do
// NOT pin offsets here so this difference is invisible to FileCheck.
//
// Per `lang.ebnf §7`:
//   function_definition = ( "func" | "function" ) scoped_identifier
//                         action_statement ;
//
// and `S26`:
//   "func" ≡ "function". The Sema-time canonicalization warning
//   ("prefer `func`") is M3's responsibility — at M2 the parser
//   accepts either spelling and produces the same AST node kind
//   (`FuncDefn`).
//
// **Failing-state evidence (FR-029)**: same as `pass-func.test` —
// the M1 driver lacks `-emit=ast`, so the FileCheck pipeline fails
// against the unchanged tree at `7bc1aea`. Once Track D (parser
// implementation) lands, BOTH this fixture and `pass-func.test`
// turn green together — that is the FR-016 / S26 parser-equivalence
// observation.

// RUN: printf 'module m {\n  function ready { }\n}\n' > %t.nsl
// RUN: %nslc -emit=ast %t.nsl | FileCheck %s

// Same node-kind sequence as the companion `pass-func.test`:
// `CompilationUnit` → `ModuleBlock` (named `m`) → `FuncDefn` (named
// `ready`) → an empty `ParallelBlock` body. Identical structurally;
// only the source offsets differ.

// CHECK:      (CompilationUnit
// CHECK:        (ModuleBlock
// CHECK-SAME:   name=m
// CHECK:          (FuncDefn
// CHECK:            (ParallelBlock
